byline.original: By MAGGIE HABERMAN and JONATHAN MARTIN

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Rodham Clinton, during speech at Iowa fundraising dinner, attacks Republican opponents but spares her Democratic rivals; by contrast, candidates Sen Bernie Sanders and former Gov Martin O'Malley, both speaking at same event, sharply criticize Clinton's record and proposals without citing her by name.
lead_paragraph: Mrs. Clinton used a speech in Des Moines to link herself closely to President Obama, but Mr. Sanders turned his sights directly on his rival.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders Attack in Iowa, but Targets Diverge
headline.print_headline: Clinton and Sanders Attack, but Targets Diverge
